sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1491036
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Constitutive Dead ER Intein T7 RNAP with YFPH
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The promoter is BBa_J23115, the RBS is BBa_B0034, the T7 RNA polymerase is BBa_K145001, the dead ER Intein is BBa_K1491026, the YFP is BBa_K864100
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: T7 RNA polymerase that contains the dead version estrogen receptor intein with a constitutive promoter. YFP is added to the end of the plasmid so that the amount of T7 RNA polymerase that is produced can be quantified through fluorescence analysis of YFP. Used as a control.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Constitutive dead ER Intein T7 RNAP with YFP for quantification of T7 RNAP to use as control for WT Intein
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Danielle Peters

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: SuperYFP2 with 6x His tag(BBa_K1491004) and a strong RBS (BBa_B0034). It can be used as a reporter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Danielle Peters
